Drove an hour from Las Cruces to see the beautiful White Sands National Park. Great wave-like dunes of gypsum sand have engulfed 275 square miles of desert, creating the world's largest gypsum dunefield!
.
You can ride horses in the park, bike, picnic, and camp backcountry style (but I’m not about that life)
.
We did a bit of sand sledding (so worth it). You can purchase sleds at the visitor center/gift shop, but the best part was the photoshoot @iambeauticurve booked for us! 
.
Great friends are hard to find and I’m grateful for the memories we made on this trip 🤍 @laydeecee @alisonlimtave @_os_vintage @iambeauticurve @kr1stalg 
.
.
.
#travel #newmexico #whitesandsnationalpark #photography #girlstrip

If you’re in LA, you have to come to @pastabarla ! This Michelin star restaurant is one for the books. You’re served a speciality cocktail upon entering the speakeasy-style venue, then you’re chauffeured over to the dining area where you’ll see chefs prepare your 11 course meal. You’re seated around an open kitchen in an intimate space with your personalized place setting. I highly recommend the reserve wine pairing! You won’t find these wines easily and they pair perfectly with each dish. The thought, love, and attention to detail at Pasta Bar is honestly perfection. 10/10 meal and experience @michelinguide #michelinrestaurant #michelinguide #restaurants #pasta

Bucket list item! Yosemite National Park is best known for its waterfalls. It’s about a 5 hour drive from Los Angeles but totally worth it! I was in Merced for a wedding, so I wanted to stop by Yosemite for the day. At the time of my visit, hurricane Hillary was passing by but luckily the storm missed us. The weather was perfect for hiking and exploring the wilderness. I’m need to come back to hike to the top of Half Dome and enjoy more than a day here. It’s truly a serene place. 
.
.
.
#california #travel #yosemite #yosemitenationalpark #california101

Photo dump of Casa Batlló in Barcelona. This place is truly a masterpiece. From 1904-1906, Antoni Gaudi completely reformed this house into a work of art using characteristics of modernist style architecture. Other prominent architects were also reforming other houses that, at the time, were competing for the urban awards convened by the Barcelona City Council. 
.
I suggest buying tickets online ahead of time to skip the long lines and go early in the AM, it’s less crowded and easier to get pictures! 
.
#travel #spain #barcelona #casabatllo #art #architecture

Barcelona photo dump!
.
My favorite recs in Barcelona:
- Casa Batllo - beautiful architecture, worth a visit. Best go to early in the morning while it’s less crowded. 
- Mercado De La Boqueria - market with food and drinks. Great place to taste a bit of everything and grab some cava. 
- El Xampanyet - best tapas place!
- Montserrat - beautiful basilica, hiking trails, local farmers produce. I recommend spending the night there because it’s a unique experience at night. It’s less touristy and you’ll get a chance to see the monks, only at night. 
- Bunkers of Carmel - best view of Barcelona. The locals don’t really like tourists coming here though. 
- Cocina Hermanos Torres - 3 star Michelin restaurant & probably the best Michelin restaurant I’ve been to.
- Two Schmucks - good drinks with good music. They play a lot of west coast hip hop. 
- Paradiso - ranked #1 on “The World’s 50 Best Bars” list. It was probably the best bar I’ve been to. Delicious cocktails, great presentation and storytelling, and upbeat energy ! 
.
#travel #spain #barcelona

Can we talk about Northern Spain? It’s so beautiful and it’s my favorite area in the country. It also has so many Michelin restaurants (delicious food!), beautiful landscapes and beaches, history and culture. 
.
Some recommendations: 
- San Sebastián - cute beach town, amazing food, Konstituzio Plaza, old town, Urgull (mountain peak), Haizearen orrazia, Motako Gaztelua (castle)
- San Juan De Gaztelugatxe - recognized as one of the worlds grandest staircases. You’ve probably seen it featured in Game of Thrones! The island is connected to the mainland by a man-made stone bridge. The hike is so beautiful, with scenic ocean views. Once you reach the top, you’ll find the chapel which has a bell situated along the front of its facade. Apparently, it’s tradition to ring the bell 3 times and make a wish. The hike is free but you’ll need to reserve tickets online ahead of time. 
- Restaurant Narru - place for lunch in San Sebastián(not located by the beach/water) but the food is delicious. 
- Restaurante PORTUONDO - located in Mundaka. come here for lunch. The views are breathtaking and the food at the top level restaurant is delicious. It’s located right by a beach.
- Akelare - Michelin restaurant with great views. The views are the best part of this place. I suggest coming to the hotel just to enjoy the view. The food at the restaurant was just ok and they’re only open for dinner, so you don’t get much of a view at night. 
- Guggenheim Museum in Bilbao - the architecture of the building itself is fascinating. 
- La Rioja - wine!! This region is famous for Rioja wine, specifically the Tempranillo and Garnacha Blanca varietals. It’s one of the only 2 nationwide regions to earn a DOCa. 
.
#travel #spain #northernspain #sansebastian #gaztelugatxe

Seville 🤍 home to Flamenco dancing & bullfighting. Is it worth visiting? Yes. 
.
Some of my favs: 
- Royal Alcazar - beautiful Mudéjar style royal palace, combining Romanesque, Gothic, and Renaissance structural elements. 
- cathedral of Seville & La Giralda - the walk up to the roof is worth it for the view! 
- Parque de María Luisa - beautiful park & probably my favorite part of Seville. You can rent a rowboat if you’re feeling adventurous lol
.
#travel #spain #seville
